<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-152] Isset values do not account for null values in constructor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-152</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Say you have:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
struct Foo {
  1: string blah
}

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you generate the Java classes for this and then do something like: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Foo foo = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Foo(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then foo.__isset.blah will be true, even though the value is actually null (unset).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
